Ghana captain, Andre Ayew, is set for a shock move to the Premier League. This was disclosed by transfer guru, Fabrizio Romano, in a tweet via his Twitter account on Wednesday evening. According to Romano, Ayew, 33, is on his way to London amid interest from two Premier League clubs, including Everton. He tweeted: “André Ayew, on his way to London now to negotiate with two Premier League clubs — including Everton. “Ayew, available as free agent and open to new step.” Ayew, who last played for Al Sadd, is currently a free agent.